    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to the author's intent in its original canonical context. The movements below trace the chapter's argument through its three major literary units: the nocturnal crisis (5:1-6), the wounded search (5:7-9), and the wasf (5:10-16). Where the Hebrew idiom or word choice materially changes the English reading, a brief note follows as supplement.",
